HEADWORD: Esculin
<hw>Es*cu"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Esculic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A glucoside obtained
from the <spn>⟦AE⟧sculus hippocastanum</spn>, or horse-chestnut, and
characterized by its fine blue fluorescent solutions.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>⟦ae⟧sculin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

